Lesson 2.2 - Science

---------- [L1]

RSS feed link: [insert here]

Video link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=87wMBqwVMOk

Creators: Ruth & Nick

Framework:

- Science defined
- Science as a process
- Applying the system
- Becoming your own scientist
- Types of truth
- Designing productive experiments (hypothesis, methods, results, analysis)
- More experiments, more data, more certainty

Audio lesson notes:
- detailed notes and timestamps from the audio lesson


Experiments (nano to macro)

- Outline the experiment framework
- Write 3 examples of a personal truths you hold and 3 examples of objective truths
- What are some common examples of errors we can make when doing experiments?
- Design a 7 day experiment that requires 10 daily minutes of data collection
- Write down 6 experiments (1 per pillar) you want to do over the course of the program

Sleep Experiment
- record the quality of your sleep over 5 consecutive days

Movement Experiment
- Continue with your deep squat and dynamic squat experiments recording your continued progress


